'''Return-to-Coruscant''' was a transmission activated by [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] during [[Operation: Knightfall/Legends|Operation: Knightfall]] through the [[Jedi beacon/Legends|Jedi beacon]]. The code - an audio signal consisting of a series of accelerating beeps - would alert [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] that the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] were over, and to return to the [[Jedi Temple/Legends|Jedi Temple]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]. In truth, the code was a plot to draw in and kill any Jedi that survived [[Order 66/Legends|Order 66]]. The code would be deactivated by [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Yoda/Legends|Yoda]] during their infiltration of the temple, with Kenobi altering the beacon to send out a "run and hide" code instead.

